1
00:00:05,696 --> 00:00:09,145
We have to understand everything 
in relationship

2
00:00:09,145 --> 00:00:11,082
and in connection with Kṛṣṇa.

3
00:00:11,082 --> 00:00:14,779
[Clients of Sweetness]

4
00:00:14,779 --> 00:00:19,132
So, madhura-rasa is the supplier.

5
00:00:19,132 --> 00:00:26,079
Vātsalya, sakhya, dāsya,
śānta are clients.

6
00:00:26,879 --> 00:00:29,037
And not only that.

7
00:00:29,037 --> 00:00:34,086
It’s just like taste.
Sweet, salty … Different tastes.

8
00:00:34,086 --> 00:00:37,289
Everything can’t be sweet.

9
00:00:37,289 --> 00:00:39,851
To really enhance 
the position of sweet,

10
00:00:39,851 --> 00:00:43,302
we begin the meal 
in Bengali style,

11
00:00:43,302 --> 00:00:47,681
śuktā-śākādi bhāji nālitā kuṣmāṇḍa
[Śrī Bhoga-ārati Gīti]

12
00:00:47,681 --> 00:00:52,912
Śuktā, something bitter— 
that will be tasteful,

13
00:00:52,912 --> 00:00:59,720
cleanse the palate, and amplify
everything tasted after that.

14
00:01:00,350 --> 00:01:08,129
So, how can there be parakīya-rasa
if there aren’t others?

15
00:01:08,540 --> 00:01:13,327
Para means ‘others’, 
the sense of anothers.

16
00:01:13,327 --> 00:01:16,370
If there were no others …

17
00:01:16,370 --> 00:01:22,361
In this way you understand
the reciprocal relationship it’s enabling.

